The paper deals with the problem of graph mining, which is a common topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and data mining (cs.DS). The use of higher order logic and specification systems also suggests a connection to logic and computation (cs.LO) and databases (cs.DB). Finally, the problem of finding frequent subgraphs is related to computational geometry (cs.CG).
